mm_data = []
def follow_market_approach(tickdata, localorders):
    # define vars
    reaction_time = 10
    PIP = 0.0001
    oindex = 0
    tindex = 0
    inventory = 0
    total_pnl = 0
    while tindex < len(tickdata):
        tick_time = tickdata.loc[tindex, 'DateTime']
        if oindex == len(localorders):
            print(total_pnl)
            break
        order_time , order_type = localorders.loc[oindex, 'Time'], localorders.loc[oindex, 'Side']
        while(tick_time > order_time):
            tempindex = len(mm_data) - 1
            mm_time = mm_data[tempindex][0]
            while(mm_time > order_time):
                tempindex -=1
                mm_time = mm_data[tempindex][0]
            # now we have the correct mm_time and tempindex a.k.a mm_index, we can take out the prices
            mm_ask = mm_data[tempindex][1]
            mm_bid = mm_data[tempindex][2]
            mm_mid = (mm_ask + mm_bid) / 2
            
            # calculate current market price from order time
            market_index = tindex - 1
            market_ask = tickdata.loc[market_index, 'Ask']
            market_bid = tickdata.loc[market_index, 'Bid']
            market_mid = (market_ask + market_bid) / 2
            market_time = tickdata.loc[market_index, 'DateTime']
            
            
            # now execute the order
            if order_type == 'B':
                pnl = mm_ask - market_mid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'pnl'] = pnl
                total_pnl += pnl
                inventory -= 1
                orders.loc[oindex, 'execution_price'] = mm_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_time'] = mm_time
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_ask'] = mm_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_bid'] = mm_bid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_time'] = market_time
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_ask'] = market_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_bid'] = market_bid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'inventory'] = inventory
                orders.loc[oindex, 'total_pnl'] = total_pnl
                mm_data.append((order_time + td(0,0.01), mm_ask, mm_bid)) # promote others to sell us

            elif order_type == 'S':
                pnl = market_mid - mm_bid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'pnl'] = pnl
                total_pnl += pnl
                inventory +=1
                orders.loc[oindex, 'execution_price'] = mm_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_time'] = mm_time
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_ask'] = mm_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_bid'] = mm_bid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_time'] = market_time
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_ask'] = market_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_bid'] = market_bid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'inventory'] = inventory
                orders.loc[oindex, 'total_pnl'] = total_pnl
                mm_data.append((order_time + td(0,0.01), mm_ask, mm_bid))
            else:
                pass
            oindex += 1
            if oindex == len(localorders):
                break
            order_time , order_type = localorders.loc[oindex, 'Time'], localorders.loc[oindex, 'Side']
            
        mm_data.append((tick_time + td(0,0.01) , tickdata.loc[tindex, 'Ask'], tickdata.loc[tindex, 'Bid']))
        tindex +=1

mm_data = []
def market_maker_approach(tickdata, localorders):
    # define vars
    reaction_time = 10
    PIP = 0.0002
    oindex = 0
    tindex = 0
    inventory = 0
    THI = 8
    execution_probability = 0
    strategy = None
    last_strategy = None
    last_order_type = None
    last_execution_probability = None
    mm_ask = 0
    mm_bid = 0
    total_pnl = 0
    while tindex < len(tickdata):
        tick_time = tickdata.loc[tindex, 'DateTime']
        if oindex == len(localorders):
            print(total_pnl)
            break
        # calculate current market price from order time
        market_index = 0 if tindex == 0 else tindex - 1
        market_ask = tickdata.loc[market_index, 'Ask']
        market_bid = tickdata.loc[market_index, 'Bid']
        market_mid = (market_ask + market_bid) / 2
        
        order_time , order_type = localorders.loc[oindex, 'Time'], localorders.loc[oindex, 'Side']
        while(tick_time > order_time):
            tempindex = len(mm_data) - 1
            mm_time = mm_data[tempindex][0]
            while(mm_time > order_time):
                tempindex -=1
                mm_time = mm_data[tempindex][0]
            # now we have the correct mm_time and tempindex a.k.a mm_index, we can take out the prices
            mm_ask = mm_data[tempindex][1]
            mm_bid = mm_data[tempindex][2]
            mm_mid = (mm_ask + mm_bid) / 2
            
            # calculate current market price from order time
            market_index = tindex - 1
            market_ask = tickdata.loc[market_index, 'Ask']
            market_bid = tickdata.loc[market_index, 'Bid']
            market_mid = (market_ask + market_bid) / 2
            market_time = tickdata.loc[market_index, 'DateTime']
            
            last_strategy = strategy
            # find our position according to the market
            if order_type == 'B':
                if mm_ask < market_ask:
                    strategy = 'inside'
                elif mm_ask == market_ask:
                    strategy = 'at'
                else:
                    strategy = 'outside'
            else:
                if mm_bid > market_bid:
                    strategy = 'inside'
                elif mm_bid == market_bid:
                    strategy = 'at'
                else:
                    strategy = 'outside'
                    
            # now calculate the probability
            execute = False
            if strategy == 'outside':
                execution_probability = 0
                execute = False
            elif strategy == 'at':
                execution_probability = 0.5
                if execution_probability < random.random():
                    execute = False
                else:
                    execute = True
            else:
                if last_order_type == order_type and last_strategy == 'inside':
                    execution_probability = 0.25
                    if execution_probability < random.random():
                        execute = True
                    else:
                        execute = False
                else:
                    execution_probability = 1
                    execute = True
            
            # now execute the order
            if execute:
                if order_type == 'B':
                    last_order_type = order_type
                    pnl = mm_ask - market_mid
                    orders.loc[oindex, 'pnl'] = pnl
                    total_pnl += pnl
                    inventory -= 1
                    orders.loc[oindex, 'execution_price'] = mm_ask

                elif order_type == 'S':
                    last_order_type = order_type
                    pnl = market_mid - mm_bid
                    orders.loc[oindex, 'pnl'] = pnl
                    total_pnl += pnl
                    inventory += 1
                    orders.loc[oindex, 'execution_price'] = mm_bid
                else:
                    pass
                orders.loc[oindex, 'executed'] = execute
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_time'] = mm_time
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_ask'] = mm_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_bid'] = mm_bid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'strategy'] = strategy
                orders.loc[oindex, 'total_pnl'] = total_pnl
                orders.loc[oindex, 'inventory'] = inventory
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_ask'] = market_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_bid'] = market_bid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_time'] = market_time
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_mid'] = market_mid
                # update market maker tape according to total_pnl and open_position
                if inventory > THI:
                    # we will favor buy orders
                    mm_ask = market_ask - PIP
                    mm_bid = market_bid - (2*PIP)
                elif inventory < (-1*THI):
                    # we will favor sell orders
                    mm_ask = market_ask + (2*PIP)
                    mm_bid = market_bid + PIP
                elif total_pnl > 0:
                    # we will try to be at market
                    mm_ask = market_ask
                    mm_bid = market_bid
                else:
                    mm_ask = market_ask - PIP
                    mm_bid = market_bid + PIP
                mm_data.append((order_time + td(0,0.01), mm_ask, mm_bid,market_ask,market_bid))
            else:
                orders.loc[oindex, 'executed'] = execute
                orders.loc[oindex, 'pnl'] = None
                orders.loc[oindex, 'execution_price'] = None
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_time'] = mm_time
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_ask'] = mm_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'mm_bid'] = mm_bid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'strategy'] = strategy
                orders.loc[oindex, 'total_pnl'] = total_pnl
                orders.loc[oindex, 'inventory'] = inventory
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_ask'] = market_ask
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_bid'] = market_bid
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_time'] = market_time
                orders.loc[oindex, 'market_mid'] = market_mid
            oindex += 1
            if oindex == len(localorders):
                break
            order_time , order_type = localorders.loc[oindex, 'Time'], localorders.loc[oindex, 'Side']
            
        if inventory > THI:
            # we will favor buy orders
            mm_ask = market_ask - PIP
            mm_bid = market_bid - (2*PIP)
        elif inventory < (-1*THI):
            # we will favor sell orders
            mm_ask = market_ask + (2*PIP)
            mm_bid = market_bid + PIP
        elif total_pnl > 0:
            # we will try to be at market
            mm_ask = market_ask
            mm_bid = market_bid
        else:
            mm_ask = market_ask - PIP
            mm_bid = market_bid + PIP
        mm_data.append((tick_time + td(0,0.01), mm_ask, mm_bid,market_ask,market_bid))
        tindex +=1
